    <title>Create Folder</title>
  </properties>

  <body>
    <section name="Create Folder">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to create a folder for contributors to put content in.</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=50;
    bottompx=550;
   </script>
   <div class='group'> 
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M9/editors/create_folder.png" alt='Create folder screenshot'/> 
    </div></div>
     <p>
      Creation of a <a href='../concepts/folder.html'>folder</a> with name 'newspaper',
      which is a folder for documents. There is already a folder for documents with name 'intern'.
     </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    In the <a href='../../contributors/concepts/folder_navigation_panel.html'>folder navigation panel</a>,
    click on 'documents' to open the documents <a href='../../contributors/concepts/slider.html'>slider</a>. Then
    open the <a href='../../contributors/concepts/folder_action_menu.html'>folder action menu</a> and choose 'create folder'
    by clicking on it. A dialog window appears.
   </p>
   <p>
    Type a descriptive name for the new folder.
   </p>
   <p>
    Root folders within a <a href='../../contributors/concepts/slider.html'>slider</a> are not created via
    a folder action menu, but via the 'Add root folder' button.
    You can see it in the screenshot for <a href='../../contributors/concepts/slider.html'>sliders</a>.
   </p>

